rComments: Michel Lord was very genuine and approachable. He cared about his students and was available to give help when needed. I would recommend that his lectures use power points or perhaps more writing on the board so that it could be easier to follow along, but overall he was very knowledgeable about the literary works that we read.
teacherRatingTags: ['Caring', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: He is a stickler for grammar. Go with a safe thesis and prove it well with good grammar, and you'll do well on your essays. Lectures are quite dull. Attendance  10 % of your mark, go to class!!

rComments: I love this prof! He is very friendly and passionate about the French language. This is the second class I have with him and he is great! He is very fair with his students, does not cut you off on presentations, and gives you extra time for assignments when needed. The only thing, he is very strict when correcting written work.

the most boring man i have ever met! no substance to his lectures at all! wanted to shoot myself in the head in lecture. unfair marker who claims that the subjects of essays are free to interpretation, when he gave me a 50 for an essay because he did not agree on my thesis argument!!!not at all impressed.
